```java
while (a &lt;= 450) {
    a = -40 + (5 * z);
    b = fahrenheit(a, b);
    System.out.printf(&quot; %-10s  %4f| %-10s  %4f&quot;, a, b, a, c);
    System.out.println(&quot;&quot;);

    z++;
}
```

&gt; _&#39;Temperature Conversion not working, all results 1 &quot;slot&quot; off being correct ...&#39;_

I&#39;m not sure if you are referring to the formatting, or part of the math.

If you are referring to the math, the _celsius_ equation is incorrect.  
_[Wikipedia &amp;ndash; Conversion of scales of temperature](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conversion_of_scales_of_temperature)_.

Here is the correct equation,

```java
public static double celsius(double z) {
    return (z * 9 / 5) + 32;
}
```

For the formatting, it looks like you&#39;ll need to use the _width_ and _precision_ format-specifiers.

There is a full list of format-specifiers on the _Formatter_ _JavaDoc_ page.  
_[Formatter (Java SE 20 &amp;amp; JDK 20)](https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/20/docs/api/java.base/java/util/Formatter.html)_

To match the expected output, I had to adjust your header fields.

```java
System.out.printf(&quot;       Temperature      |       Temperature%n&quot;);
System.out.printf(&quot;        (degrees)       |        (degrees) %n&quot;);
System.out.printf(&quot;      F           C     |      C           F%n&quot;);
```

And then, I used _%10.3f_, which will use _10_ total characters, and 3 decimal values.

Additionally, you&#39;re going to want to evaluate _a_ first, within the _loop_.  
And, I removed the unnecessary _b_ parameter from the _fahrenheit_ method.

```java
while (a &lt;= 450) {
    a = -40 + (5 * z);
    b = fahrenheit(a);
    System.out.printf(&quot;%10.3f  %10.3f  |&quot;, a, b);
    c = celsius(b);
    System.out.printf(&quot;%10.3f  %10.3f%n&quot;, b, c);
    z++;
}
```

Here is the full re-factor.

```java
public static void main (String[] args) {
    double a = 0;
    double b = 0;
    double c = 0;
    double z = 0;
    System.out.printf(&quot;       Temperature      |       Temperature%n&quot;);
    System.out.printf(&quot;        (degrees)       |        (degrees) %n&quot;);
    System.out.printf(&quot;      F           C     |      C           F%n&quot;);

    z = 0;
    while (a &lt;= 450) {
        a = -40 + (5 * z);
        b = fahrenheit(a);
        System.out.printf(&quot;%10.3f  %10.3f  |&quot;, a, b);
        c = celsius(b);
        System.out.printf(&quot;%10.3f  %10.3f%n&quot;, b, c);
        z++;
    }
}

public static double fahrenheit(double a) {
    return ((a-32)*5)/9;
}

public static double celsius(double z) {
    return (z * 9 / 5) + 32;
}
```

