You are right that `src/it` is intended to be used for integrations test of plugins. This is mentioned in the [Standard Directory Layout](https://maven.apache.org/guides/introduction/introduction-to-the-standard-directory-layout.html).

The `maven-failsafe-plugin`, by default, will look for your integration tests inside [`${project.build.testSourceDirectory}`](http://maven.apache.org/surefire/maven-failsafe-plugin/integration-test-mojo.html#testSourceDirectory), [which is the same](http://maven.apache.org/surefire/maven-surefire-plugin/test-mojo.html#testSourceDirectory) as the `maven-surefire-plugin` for unit tests. By default, this corresponds to `src/test/java`. The integration tests are made distinct by following a [naming convention](http://maven.apache.org/surefire/maven-failsafe-plugin/integration-test-mojo.html#includes):

    &lt;includes&gt;
      &lt;include&gt;**/IT*.java&lt;/include&gt;
      &lt;include&gt;**/*IT.java&lt;/include&gt;
      &lt;include&gt;**/*ITCase.java&lt;/include&gt;
    &lt;/includes&gt;

which is different than the [naming convention](http://maven.apache.org/surefire/maven-surefire-plugin/test-mojo.html#includes) for unit-tests:

    &lt;includes&gt;
      &lt;include&gt;**/Test*.java&lt;/include&gt;
      &lt;include&gt;**/*Test.java&lt;/include&gt;
      &lt;include&gt;**/*TestCase.java&lt;/include&gt;
    &lt;/includes&gt;

So while they would reside in the same source folder (`src/test/java`), the difference in names clearly distinguishes them. Also, this is the default set-up so no extra configuration would be needed.

That said, you can have other options:

 - Place the integration tests inside a different source folder. This will require some configuration to make it work: you will need to use the [`build-helper-maven-plugin:add-test-source`](http://www.mojohaus.org/build-helper-maven-plugin/add-test-source-mojo.html) goal to add the custom folder as a test source folder.
 - Use a different module (if you have a multi-module Maven project) that would only contain the integration tests.

